{
  "bookId": "heshanggong-laozi",
  "num": 45,
  "title": "第四十五章（洪德）",
  "author": "老子",
  "authorId": "Laozi",
  "dynasty": "周",
  "era": "周",
  "genre": "prose",
  "verses": [
    {
      "text": "大成若缺，"
    },
    {
      "text": "其用不弊，"
    },
    {
      "text": "大盈若沖，"
    },
    {
      "text": "其用不窮。"
    },
    {
      "text": "大直若屈，"
    },
    {
      "text": "大巧若拙，"
    },
    {
      "text": "大辯若訥。"
    },
    {
      "text": "躁勝寒，"
    },
    {
      "text": "靜勝熱，"
    },
    {
      "text": "清靜能為天下正。"
    }
  ],
  "sections": {},
  "annotations": [],
  "layers": {
    "heshanggong": [
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "謂道德大成之君也。 若缺者，滅名藏譽，如毀缺不備也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "其用心如是，則無敝盡時也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "謂道德大盈滿之君也。 若沖者，貴不敢驕也，富不敢奢也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "其用心如是，則無窮盡時也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 4,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "大直，謂修道法度正直如一也。 若屈者，不與俗人爭，若可屈折。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 5,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "大巧謂多才術也。 若拙者，亦不敢見其能。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-7",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 6,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "大辯者，智無疑。若訥者，口無辟",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-8",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 7,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 4
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "勝，極也。春夏陽氣躁疾於上，萬物盛大，極則寒，寒則零落死亡也。言人不當剛躁也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-9",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 8,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 4
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "秋冬萬物靜於黃泉之下，極則熱，熱者生之源。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-10",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 9,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 8
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "能清靜則為天下之長，持身正則無終已時也。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ]
  },
